Not a dry eye in the house as Vietnam Vets received a special Presidential commendation at the Veterans History Project event in Bellevue. We owe our Vietnam Veterans so much. pic.twitter.com/OHxA1DUmyq

What a remarkable day. We recorded the stories of Nebraska's veterans as part of the Library of Congress Veterans History Project. If you know a veteran who'd like to share their story, please contact my Lincoln office. @librarycongress pic.twitter.com/OVKaPckobc

Amid the nasty partisan arguments in DC this week, I stood outside the Capitol with Republicans and Democrats to speak about a new service idea available to our #Vets. It doesn’t involve traditional treatments, buildings or drugs. It involves service dogs. https://bit.ly/34brwAs

If you are a veteran, I invite you to share your story as part of the Veterans History Project, Tuesday, Nov 26 in Bellevue or Lincoln (details below). This important event will also include a special presentation on "Preserving the Legacy of D-Day.” #Veterans pic.twitter.com/vCmmQQSdi9

I have agreed to cosponsor Protecting America's Food and Agriculture Act.  The bill authorizes U.S. Customs and Border Protection to hire more ag inspectors in order to help prevent an outbreak of African swine fever in the U.S.

On this day, 42 years ago, Egypt President Anwar Sadat, in a remarkable act of courage, became the first Arab leader to visit Israel. He said, “I have come to you so that together we should build a durable peace based on justice.”

Pleased to support the Workplace Violence Prevention for Health Care and Social Service Workers Act. These workers provide critical care to the sick and elderly, yet violence against them is rising. This bill puts in place preventative procedures to reverse this trend.

I'm lead co-sponsor of a bill to resume sales of the Save Vanishing Species Stamp, which comes to the floor this week. Sales of these stamps have raised nearly $6M for global conservation projects, including for sea turtles, great apes, elephants, tigers, rhinos #conservation

Congratulations to Admiral Charles Richard as he takes command at Stratcom—and all the best to General Hyten as he transitions to the Joint Chiefs of Staff.  Extraordinarily moving ceremony today at the new Stratcom headquarters. @US_Stratcom #strategicdeterrence pic.twitter.com/pc4lZ13S7x
